{{define "working-conventions"}}
WORKING CONVENTIONS:
- Read nearby files in the same feature area before editing. Match the patterns already dominant there.
- Extract helpers only when reuse is real — not preemptively.
- Keep diffs focused: additive changes for the task. No drive-by refactors, renames, or reformatting of untouched code.
- Before committing, scan the diff: if most changed lines are moves, renames, or style-only churn rather than new behavior, narrow the change.
- Handle errors at system boundaries; return safe outcomes for expected failure paths instead of crashing user flows when the codebase already does that.
{{end}}
